=head1 DESCRIPTION

Information about the schema status.

A status of C<READY> means that based on the schema analysis rule,
queries of the given analysis rule type are properly configured to run
queries on this schema.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AnalysisRuleType => Str

The analysis rule type for which the schema status has been evaluated.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AnalysisType => Str

The type of analysis that can be performed on the schema.

A schema can have an C<analysisType> of C<DIRECT_ANALYSIS>,
C<ADDITIONAL_ANALYSIS_FOR_AUDIENCE_GENERATION>, or both.


=head2 Configurations => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The configuration details of the schema analysis rule for the given
type.


=head2 Reasons => ArrayRef[L<Paws::CleanRooms::SchemaStatusReason>]

The reasons why the schema status is set to its current state.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Status => Str

The status of the schema, indicating if it is ready to query.



